items.title: 4 People Injured After Stabbing Outside Manchester Synagogue, UK Police Say
items.description: The stabbing in Manchester, England, came on Yom Kippur, the holiest day in the Jewish calendar.

items.title: Madagascar’s President Rajoelina Dissolved His Government, but Calls for His Resignation Continue
items.description: A growing protest movement on the African island, despite deadly clashes with security forces, vows to keep fighting until Andry Rajoelina is ousted.

items.title: A Run on Canned Mackerel and Emergency Radios. The Reason? Drones.
items.description: The Danish public has been unsettled by a wave of mysterious drone incursions, which has underscored the country’s vulnerability.

items.title: Many Palestinians Say Hamas Must Accept U.S. Cease-Fire Plan
items.description: Interviews in Gaza suggest wide support for a proposal that calls for an immediate end to a war that has brought immense civilian suffering.
